<div class="body">
<h1>Documenting Cinelerra's source code</h1>

<div class="boxa">
<p>Cinelerra's source code consists of a many, <em>many</em>
lines of code, spread over thousands of files.  Getting up
to speed by simply looking through the code takes months,
even for a skilled programmer.</p>
</div>

 <div class="boxb">
<h2>Automatic documentation</h2>

<p>There are quick ways of producing cross-references
 and pretty dependency graphs out of raw source code.
 We will use that as a foundation.  So far, I have used
 <a href="http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/">Doxygen</a>.
</p>
</div>

<div class="boxa">
<h2>API documentation, examples, test applications</h2>

<p>To come, I hope...</p>
</div>

<div class="boxb">
<h2>Doxygen source code documentation</h2>

<p>I've run doxygen on the <a href="doxy/a118/guicast/html/">
guicast subdirectory</a> and the <a href="doxy/a118/cinelerra/html/">
cinelerra subdirectory</a> of the source code.  Cinelerra's core and GUI
code can now be examined more conveniently.</p>

<p>This is version 1.1.8 from Heroines.  Here is one
<a href="doxy/a118/guicast/Doxyfile">configuration file</a>
I used to generate it.  Thanks to Jens Seidel for suggesting
doxygen, and providing a template configuration file.</p>
</div>
 
